CC   -!- FUNCTION: Sigma factors are initiation factors that promote the
CC       attachment of RNA polymerase to specific initiation sites and are then
CC       released. This sigma factor contributes to both stress response and
CC       virulence gene expression. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:26744224}.
CC   -!- ACTIVITY REGULATION: Negatively regulated by the anti-sigma-I factor
CC       RsgI. {ECO:0000255|HAMAP-Rule:MF_02064, ECO:0000269|PubMed:26744224}.
CC   -!- SUBUNIT: Interacts with RsgI. {ECO:0000255|HAMAP-Rule:MF_02064}.
CC   -!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Cytoplasm {ECO:0000255|HAMAP-Rule:MF_02064}.
CC   -!- INDUCTION: Part of the sigI-rsgI operon, which is induced by heat
CC       shock. Expressed from both the sigma I and sigma A promoters.
CC       Transcription from the sigma A promoter is likely more significant to
CC       virulence regulation. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:26744224}.
CC   -!- DISRUPTION PHENOTYPE: Disruption results in increased sensitivity to
CC       heat shock. Loss of SigI results in a coordinated decrease in
CC       expression of all three toxin subunits. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:26744224}.
CC   -!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the sigma-70 factor family. SigI subfamily.
CC       {ECO:0000255|HAMAP-Rule:MF_02064}.
